  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Of the silver, all that is mentioned is the amount of atonement-money raised from those who were numbered (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 30:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) at the rate of half a shekel for every male, without including the freewill-offerings of silver (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 35:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 25:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), whether it was that they were too insignificant, or that they were not used for the work, but were placed with the excess mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 36:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The result of the numbering gave 603,550 men, every one of whom paid half a shekel. This would yield 301,775 shekels, or 100 talents and 1775 shekels, which proves by the way that a talent contained 3000 shekels. A hundred talents of this were used for casting 96 sockets for the 48 boards, and 4 sockets for the 4 pillars of the inner court, - one talent therefore for each socket, - and the 1775 shekels for the hooks of the pillars that sustained the curtains, for silvering their capitals, and \"for binding the pillars,\" i.e., for making the silver connecting rods for the pillars of the court (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 27:10-11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
